## API Reference

### Banner

Displays contextual inline messages for informational, alert, or error states.

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `variant` | `"default" \| "alert" \| "error"` | No | Visual style. Defaults to `"default"`. |
| `icon` | `Snippet` | No | Icon snippet rendered before the banner content. |
| `title` | `string` | No | Structured banner title. |
| `description` | `Snippet \| string` | No | Structured banner description. |
| `action` | `Snippet` | No | Action area rendered at the end of structured banners. |
| `children` | `Snippet` | No | Legacy simple banner content when `title` and `description` are not provided. |
| `text` | `string` | No | Fallback simple text content when no children are provided. |
| `class` | `string` | No | Additional classes merged with the banner styles. |

All other props are passed to the underlying `<div>` element.
